Prague public transport on Wednesday for the first time will also drive on a chip
Wednesday 1 October 2008 will be recorded in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date when the first passengers will enter the metro, tram and buses, who will have an electronic coupon in their pocket instead of a paper ticket.
At the moment, it can buy about one hundred thousand people who own an Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a 30-day and 90-day and annual coupon (which will be valid from January 1, 2009) and at the same time have it recorded on their chip card in the information centers and workplaces of the Transport Company in the metro stations Muzeum, M<0xC5><0xAF>stek, Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice Railway Station, And<0xC4><0x9B>l, Roztyly, Let<0xC5><0x88>any, Kobylisy, Paradise Garden, Ka<0xC4><0x8D>erov and Luka.
Coupons can be purchased from yesterday via the Internet on the website of the Transport Company www.dpp.cz.
More than 400 customers used the service by the afternoon.
Those who start using the online store can definitely forget about the dispensing windows in the metro stations, where they still had to stand regularly in long queues for paper tickets.
They buy the coupon online and upload it to their Opencard card at one of the 13 branches of the City Library.
"In these places, passengers have access to a desk with trained staff, which will help them with their online purchase and will also upload a purchased coupon to their card," Martin Opatrn<0xC3><0xBD>, a spokesman for the project, said.
In addition to libraries, it will be possible to upload electronic coupons to Opencard also in self-service vending machines, which are mounted in several vestibules of the metro.
What do these machines look like?
They are red, they resemble ticket markers, and passengers may have already noticed them in the metro stations Roztyly, Bud<0xC4><0x9B>jovick<0xC3><0xA1>, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavsk<0xC3><0xA1>.
"There are five in the city now, but by the end of the year there should be eighty," he added.
Coupon will check the place of the driver of the vending machine
The operation of the vending machines that will start working tomorrow is simple.
Just insert an Opencard chip card into them and the previously paid coupon will upload itself.
