Jeremiah Moss, who writes a blog called Jeremiah’s Disappearing New York (subtitled “The Book of Weeping: A Bitter Nostalgic View of the City in the Process of Extinction”), posted part of the story about Extra Place from the Let’s Talk About the City section, which appeared in The New Yorker in 1952.
The author of the article, Brendan Gill, wrote: "Extra Place is a narrow dead end, dark even in the daytime and bounded by rusty iron doors of warehouses and clogged windows, where a week old newspaper runs in the rafters."
Except for a few exceptions, the alley looked exactly the same on a recent night.
The rat ran through the blind end of the street near the door that once led to the CBGB, where today there is an expensive clothing store.
