It’s Open Office.org 3.0, an open source personal production package that aims to infiltrate more and more users, from home to office, from experts to public administration, as a free alternative to the more familiar Microsoft Office.
After about a year of volunteer work, controlled by the SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office is shown to the general public with various novelties: the welcome screen and the revised and improved opening window will be added to other, much more essential, such as compatibility for the Apple Mac OS X operating system and support for the new ODF format (Open Document Format) 1.2, the latest standard ISO.
Emphasis is also placed on working with the Office 2007 package, Open Office is able to open the document even with the new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx).
Interesting are the special features of some models, such as what allows you to reduce the size of a PowerPoint presentation, useful for example for electronic transmission, or the ability to transfer a PDF folder to a graphical model and preserve the original appearance of the page.
From this point of view, we can still create "PDF hybrids" documents that resemble typical Adobe graphics and have the features of a spreadsheet or text program.
Cooperation is an element that has received many improvements within application programs: in Excel, it is possible to work together between different users and avoid conflicts on changes, in a text program, each co-worker is assigned one color for comments to be more clearly identified in the revision phase.
Some companies are also working to transfer some of the Open Office features to the Web (on the cloud), and in the coming weeks they should remake the definitive result.
The Italian version can be downloaded at http://it.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html, it has been added to the English version, which has been on the mirror since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, as usual, the package is also available for the Linux operating system.
Also, the installation CD can be sent home or to the workplace on request.
And if the topic of freeness can be a tactic to expand in households, it is the Open Office business area that the package bets a lot, and it can already count on a variety of projects implemented in public administration and in schools.
And there are also offers of training, consultation and assistance services ideal for small and medium-sized businesses, which could open up business perspectives.
Open Office consists of five main models: Writer, for video typing replacing Word; Calc is a spreadsheet processor that aims to replace Excel; Impress for PowerPoint-like presentations; Dbase, as in the case of the more famous Access, is a program that allows you to work on databases; Draw, in the end, is a graphical model.
The goal for 2008 is to reach 5 million downloads, and if we consider that today we are almost 3 million and 600,000, with the release of the new version, it is possible that this estimated number can even be exceeded.
